Secondary Spells: 0 <br>
Specialization Mean: 7 <br>
Direct Damage Shout I, Direct Damage Shout II, Group HP Regen, Group Speed Enhance, Instant Stun, Group Add Damage, Snare <br>
<br>
Bard Nurture, Regrowth, Music: <br>
Secondary Spells: 8 <br>
Specialization Mean: 3 <br>
(Secondary) AF Buff, STR Buff, DEX Buff. Heal, Greater Heal, Resurrect I, Mesmerize, Amnesia <br>
(Nurture) Group Regen Fatigue, Group Speed Enhance, Group Power Regen <br>
(Regrowth) Major Heal, Group Regen Health, Group Heal <br>
(Bard Music) Direct Damage, AE Mesmerize, Confusion <br>
<br>
Warden Nurture, Regrowth: <br>
Secondary Spells: 6 <br>
Specialization Mean: 4 <br>
(Secondary) AF buff, STR buff, DEX buff, Heal, Greater Heal, Resurrect I <br>
(Nurture) Absorb Shield, Self Haste, Group Enhance Speed, Group Enhance Add Damage <br>
(Regrowth) Self Fatigue Regen, Major Heal, Self Health Regen, Resurrect II <br>
<br>
Wardens at first seem out of place, but they share many traits with the Bard classes. In addition to 1.5x specialization, they have some combat abilities and some spell abilities, much like a blend of Skald and Bard. They share an issue that bards have which I will address later. <br>
<br>
Out of the bard classes, Minstrels and Skalds are best equipped, with Bards slightly behind. Upon specialization, Minstrels get access to 9 specialization spells, all of which are useful spells that we have become familiar to associate with Bard like classes. The rest of the Minstrels points can be spent in Stealth or Melee. Skalds get 7 specialization spells, with almost all except Snare as being very useful. <br>
<br>
Bards work very differently than the other bard classes and function almost like a spellcaster. They get access to 8 secondary spell lines just through leveling, with Mesmerize, Amnesia, and Healing being the most useful of the bunch along with individual stat buffs. After that, the Bard gets 3 specialization spell lines and weaker access to 3 specialization spells. This allows them to live up to their realm comparative role as having more magical ability at the cost of melee. <br>
<br>
Wardens are the best equipped out of this class comparison. Also the Warden has access to 6 secondary spells without specialization. I’ve spoke with different Wardens, and some opt to forgo any kind of melee specialization and spend it on both of their spell specialization options. Soloing is possible if the Warden specializes in Nurture and melee skills. Their damage output in pure melee is less than a tank and almost like that of a bard type with a weapon skill, but head on they would lose to a pure or hybrid tank. They are also have a group support role as buffer and healer. Wardens are balanced with respect to other classes in general, and as having a role in their realm. <br>
<br>
The Albion Minstrel is well equipped, has the core bard spells that makes the class an important group supporter, but faces the problem of weapon and instrument swapping. This hindrance alone is enough to set back the Minstrel as slightly under par, with 3.5 points. <br>
<br>
Skalds come from Midgard, so they are expected to be better at melee and to have less spell ability. This holds true for the most part, except they do not have that much of a melee advantage overall (except that they don’t have to swap instruments). I would recommend bumping Evade to II or allowing Medium Shield and a base for Shield Specialization so they get an additional 5% bonus, even without putting any points into it, after all they do come from the way of the Viking. Until they get a melee enhancement that represents their realm, I score them at 3.5. <br>
<br>
The Bard of Hibernia lives up to its role as being the most magical of all the Bards at the cost of melee altogether. They often have to swap multiple instruments and almost never engage in melee. It is however problematic having a host of secondary spells, while the best Bard spells are separated by different specialization areas, whereas the other bards have a single area of specialization. On paper, it looks powerful, but in reality Bards are making a melee sacrifice that the other two realm bards do not have to make. Altogether though, they have it slightly better than their bard counterparts, and are balanced with respect to their realm role. <br>
<br>
MINSTREL: 3 <br>
SKALD: 3 <br>
BARD: 3.5 <br>
WARDEN: 4 <br>
<br>
<br>
