I’m going to keep this section short since Archers have been looked at in depth a lot and there are still more nerfs going on along with promised future enhancements (tracking, shapeshifting Hunters). I’ll sum up differences in brief: <br>
<br>
The Scout has the best nonmagical abilities and has the best bow by two paces, however they lack any magic, so their points are diverted towards melee after Stealth and Longbow. <br>
<br>
The Hunter has a combination of Self Buffs and Pet Spells, making them somewhat of an enhanced archer, but the pet is almost useless and neglected for PVP purposes. <br>
<br>
The Ranger is the ultimate self buff enhancing archer of the 3 and are the most capable in PVP. When it comes to Archer VS Archer though, it often does not matter which class you are, it’s all about who detects who first. <br>
<br>
As was stated by Sanya, all the archers were unfinished in beta and they got a damage bonus to compensate for that, which was overlooked up until this point. It’s Nerf effect has yet to be seen and is being tested on Pendragon. Until then, I’m scoring them with the current archer damage bonus in tact pre-nerf. PVE however, all the archers are more balanced in that respect, but the current state of their PVP can’t be ignored: <br>
<br>
SCOUT: 4.5 <br>
HUNTER: 5.0 <br>
RANGER: 5.5 <br>
<br>
<br>
