<br>
I posted a thorough analysis of the class at: <br>
vnboards.ign.com/message....c=19406566 <br>
<br>
The primary difference between the classes is the fact that the Nightshade gets a weak DD in place of a ranged weapon. Also worth noting is the Left Axe issue and lack of Thrusting weapons in Midgard. However, Shadowblades have found that 2hs weapons can perform “relatively” devastating backstabs (still week compared to tank styles), and they are the only of the Assassin classes to get to use 2-handed weapons. Also plaguing this class is the need for too many skills and not enough points. All the Assassins are on par with each other (which is a very low standard), but serve no role in their realms. <br>
<br>
INFILTRATOR: 1 <br>
SHADOWBLADE: 1 <br>
NIGHTSHADE: 1 <br>
<br>
<br>
*** CLERIC, HEALER, DRUID *** <br>
<br>
CLERIC: Chain Mail, Medium Shield <br>
HEALER: Chain Mail, Small Shield <br>
DRUID: Scale Mail, Small Shield <br>
<br>
